      • writeToFile

        public void writeToFile(Model model,
                        java.lang.String filePath)
        This method takes a Model object and writes it to the file, specified by the filePath and the FILENAME. If no file exists when this method is called, a new file will be created.
        Parameters:
        model - Model object in question. If none, new will be created.
        filePath - File path in question. (Default: Empty = Project folder)
